title:          "Identity affecting situations and the Dictator's game"
date:           2025-04-01 00:01:00 +0800
selected:       false
type:           "Work in Progress"
# pub:            "AEJ: Applied Economics (forthcoming)"
# pub_pre:        "Submitted"
# pub_post:       'Under review.'
pub_last:       "(Draft in preparation)"
pub_date:       "2025"

abstract: >-
  In an online experiment, we explore distributive choices in identity-affecting vs. identity-preserving situations and intuitions about the non-identity problem. Results show individuals treat both contexts similarly, suggesting intuitive acceptance of person-affecting views and offering insights into Population Ethics and Experimental Economics.
